{"id": "ChIJgxHvsnR_j4ARtr5BoTIWlVc", "rating": 4.7, "priceLevel": "PRICE_LEVEL_MODERATE", "userRatingCount": 444, "displayName": {"text": "Al Carajo", "languageCode": "en"}, "reviews": [{"name": "places/ChIJgxHvsnR_j4ARtr5BoTIWlVc/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT25reU9FVkpaM05WWm1SUWF6bG1jVEpUTW5VNVVXYxAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a month ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "Al Carajo Yucatán is a fantastic spot for breakfast, lunch, or dinner. While I've heard people criticize the restaurant for its small dining area, I think the food more than makes up for any lack of seating comfort.\n\nAs someone who has tried chilaquiles all over the Bay Area, I can confidently say that the chilaquiles here rank in my top three. The standout is the sauce—a delicious medium-spicy, tomato-forward sauce with just the right amount of tanginess. It's layered over crispy tortillas and topped with eggs, queso cotija, crema fresca, and pickled red onions, creating a flavorful and well-balanced dish.\n\nThe portion size was generous, and the presentation was impressive. In fact, my lunch companions commented on the appearance, aroma, and overall abundance of the dish when it arrived at the table.\n\nI'll definitely be returning and bringing guests with me. Between the outstanding food and convenient location, Al Carajo Yucatán has earned a spot on my list of favorite Mexican restaurants in the area.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "Al Carajo Yucatán is a fantastic spot for breakfast, lunch, or dinner. While I've heard people criticize the restaurant for its small dining area, I think the food more than makes up for any lack of seating comfort.\n\nAs someone who has tried chilaquiles all over the Bay Area, I can confidently say that the chilaquiles here rank in my top three. The standout is the sauce—a delicious medium-spicy, tomato-forward sauce with just the right amount of tanginess. It's layered over crispy tortillas and topped with eggs, queso cotija, crema fresca, and pickled red onions, creating a flavorful and well-balanced dish.\n\nThe portion size was generous, and the presentation was impressive. In fact, my lunch companions commented on the appearance, aroma, and overall abundance of the dish when it arrived at the table.\n\nI'll definitely be returning and bringing guests with me. Between the outstanding food and convenient location, Al Carajo Yucatán has earned a spot on my list of favorite Mexican restaurants in the area.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Eddie Valadez", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105676670269792434653/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUr6I0WpsBC2xEXGs27nAB-saDmynPcb3uGsZA4W-FeKXRR88RUkA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba7"}, "publishTime": "2026-06-12T19:21:53.600073815Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT25reU9FVkpaM05WWm1SUWF6bG1jVEpUTW5VNVVXYxAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT25reU9FVkpaM05WWm1SUWF6bG1jVEpUTW5VNVVXYxAB!2m1!1s0x808f7f74b2ef1183:0x57951632a141beb6"}, {"name": "places/ChIJgxHvsnR_j4ARtr5BoTIWlVc/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xwRlYyTkNWbkIzY1RCTFdsQlZSVlF5YWt3MWJrRRAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "6 months ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "I'm not very familiar with Yucatan cuisine, but liked this place - the chicken tinga quesadilla was a personal favorite and I liked it more than their famous breakfast burrito, which was good and had a nice crunch, but was quite oily. Husband had their ceviche and it was sweeter than expected, but good. I also liked their hot sauce a lot. Dog friendly outdoor seating is a nice plus.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "I'm not very familiar with Yucatan cuisine, but liked this place - the chicken tinga quesadilla was a personal favorite and I liked it more than their famous breakfast burrito, which was good and had a nice crunch, but was quite oily. Husband had their ceviche and it was sweeter than expected, but good. I also liked their hot sauce a lot. Dog friendly outdoor seating is a nice plus.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "May Bresler Herzog", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101131407266199223711/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW3oEkCBREOQoS9leZfR6E8wga8hx3wNeuJ0qqLfaHXd9PeSAHbDA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5"}, "publishTime": "2026-01-09T22:56:17.807266887Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xwRlYyTkNWbkIzY1RCTFdsQlZSVlF5YWt3MWJrRRAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xwRlYyTkNWbkIzY1RCTFdsQlZSVlF5YWt3MWJrRRAB!2m1!1s0x808f7f74b2ef1183:0x57951632a141beb6"}, {"name": "places/ChIJgxHvsnR_j4ARtr5BoTIWlVc/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xsYWNVeHJibGhpUWprelVtVmthMmt3YlZSMFQxRRAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "3 weeks ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "The Al Carajo Taqueria is about the best thing in this neighborhood, after looking around at all the barred up storefronts and windows the only thing I could think of was...this must be what it's like to be looking into a prison!\nBut...Let me yell you, I had about the best Tacos de Pollo con Mango Salsa I've ever had!  5 ☆☆☆☆☆'s for sure!", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "The Al Carajo Taqueria is about the best thing in this neighborhood, after looking around at all the barred up storefronts and windows the only thing I could think of was...this must be what it's like to be looking into a prison!\nBut...Let me yell you, I had about the best Tacos de Pollo con Mango Salsa I've ever had!  5 ☆☆☆☆☆'s for sure!", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "American Angler", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110528677426487009216/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWCYctkW9WSngtVdHYS7nmmTl4RYD8TmmC6-BvvxZeU6DwBbO-8=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba7"}, "publishTime": "2026-06-16T16:58:09.310437637Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xsYWNVeHJibGhpUWprelVtVmthMmt3YlZSMFQxRRAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xsYWNVeHJibGhpUWprelVtVmthMmt3YlZSMFQxRRAB!2m1!1s0x808f7f74b2ef1183:0x57951632a141beb6"}, {"name": "places/ChIJgxHvsnR_j4ARtr5BoTIWlVc/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xjNVJqQk1VMFowYTBGbVpuZHVaR0Z3YmxWZlVWRRAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "7 months ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "THE BEST BREAKFAST BURRITO. Al Carajo in the Mission makes the best breakfast burrito I’ve ever had. The hash browns are cooked perfectly, crisp and structured without any grease. It’s a meat-forward burrito, but not overwhelming the way a Deli Board sandwich can be. The chipotle sauce that comes with it is ideal for drizzling and pulls the whole thing together. The staff inside is always friendly, and when I order through DoorDash it consistently arrives very warm. Call outs for the chorizo, eggs, avocado and crispy potatoes are balanced, and I agree. This burrito earns its reputation.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "THE BEST BREAKFAST BURRITO. Al Carajo in the Mission makes the best breakfast burrito I’ve ever had. The hash browns are cooked perfectly, crisp and structured without any grease. It’s a meat-forward burrito, but not overwhelming the way a Deli Board sandwich can be. The chipotle sauce that comes with it is ideal for drizzling and pulls the whole thing together. The staff inside is always friendly, and when I order through DoorDash it consistently arrives very warm. Call outs for the chorizo, eggs, avocado and crispy potatoes are balanced, and I agree. This burrito earns its reputation.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Neal Mueller", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102645031703620284067/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXgluW8gDjZvxcAaIyG6wmchK4MKVJKDIZ3YAKISChFsTq_sgoCSA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5"}, "publishTime": "2025-11-21T19:41:25.658988744Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xjNVJqQk1VMFowYTBGbVpuZHVaR0Z3YmxWZlVWRRAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xjNVJqQk1VMFowYTBGbVpuZHVaR0Z3YmxWZlVWRRAB!2m1!1s0x808f7f74b2ef1183:0x57951632a141beb6"}, {"name": "places/ChIJgxHvsnR_j4ARtr5BoTIWlVc/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2tFMFFsQnROa1pNYTB3elEwOVlPRWxOVDI1VlUxRRAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "3 months ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "Definitely a place for the quesabirria lovers, the pizza is enough for two and is a beauty. The burrito with poc chuc was also delicious, very unique citrus flavor and crispy texture. Service was friendly and good vibes all arouns.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "Definitely a place for the quesabirria lovers, the pizza is enough for two and is a beauty. The burrito with poc chuc was also delicious, very unique citrus flavor and crispy texture. Service was friendly and good vibes all arouns.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Dan Killam", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117953538048728039790/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUOrVnTFjeA01Kz__9WfaGfA463YcwfPC6XrKmTg089GGgfU62x=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo"}, "publishTime": "2026-03-29T19:06:41.534500075Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2tFMFFsQnROa1pNYTB3elEwOVlPRWxOVDI1VlUxRRAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2